Lagos – Senior Manager, Sponsorship qne Promotion, MTN Nigeria Limited, Osaze Ebueku has praised the standard of play exhibited by players at the just concluded NPFL/LaLiga Under- 15 Football Championship sponsored by his company, MTN. Speaking with our correspondent after the final of the championship, Ebueku said with what was displayed by the players, the future of football in the country is very bright. “I am highly impressed with what the players displayed since the commencement of the tournament two weeks ago and at the finals. -Advertisement- The tournament has really improved and am proud of the players that participated. “What this means is that the future of our football is very bright and we are proud in MTN as sponsors of the tournament in partnership with NPFL and LaLiga”, he said. While commending LaLiga for partnering MTN in developing football in the country, Ebueku assured that products discovered from the tournament would form a pool of players for the Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) for the national teams. In the final match of the tournament, Remo Stars defeated Shooting Stars 2-0 at the Remo Stars Stadium in Ikenne to win this year’s edition of the tournament. A brace from tournament’s top scorer Arierhi Kparobo proved enough for the Ikenne- based team to defeat the Ibadan young lads and bring an end to an exciting display of football artistry from young players. POLL Earlier in the third place match, Katsina United had defeated Kano Pillars 5-4 on penalties after the two sides played out a 2-2 draw at the regulation time. Remo Stars’ Ohamesi Chimezie won the Most Valuable Player (MVP) of the tournament award while scorer of the two goals in the final match, Kparobo emerged as the Highest Goals Scorer with five goals. The tournament saw teams from the NPFL gather present their youngsters in front of scouts for two weeks.